Slide 45: Common Mistakes

This slide is mostly talking, but you can demo two quick mistakes safely.

Mistake: Searching too broadly

Bad:

grep -R error /var/log 2>/dev/null | head

Better:

journalctl -u sshd -b --since "1 hour ago" --no-pager | tail -20

Mistake: Deleting before previewing

Bad, do not run live:

echo "find /tmp -name '*.tmp' -delete"

Better:

find /tmp/rhel-demo/tmp -name "*.tmp" -print

What it shows:
The better habit is usually just as easy as the risky habit.

